						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1293 (1371 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that <hi rend="bold">Goppaṇa</hi> took the image of Raṅganātha from Tirupati to Cheñji, his capital and after defeating the Muslims restored the image to Śrīraṅgam and had it installed there with Lakshmī and Bhūdēvī, the consorts of the Lord. The record is dated in Śaka year 1293 expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="italic">bandhupriya.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. VI, p. 322)</p>						

						</summary>
